Scope:
  Exact integer dynamic programming checks every signed word in the displayed
  finite box and every partial-character target.  For each target it compares
  the ordinary coefficient with the finite coefficients at the exact level

    K=max(max_i a_i,target,ceil((sum_i a_i+target)/2))

  and at K+1.  The below-threshold scan is diagnostic evidence for sharpness;
  the unbounded theorem is the fusion-tree argument in
  SU2_HALF_TOTAL_STABILITY_2026_07_24.md.
